\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true,\n    \"forceConsistentCasingInFileNames\": true,\n    \"resolveJsonModule\": true,\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"declarationMap\": true,\n    \"sourceMap\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*\"],\n  \"exclude\": [\"node_modules\", \"dist\", \"tests\"]\n}\n```\n\n**3. .eslintrc.cjs** (/workspace/.eslintrc.cjs)\n```javascript\nmodule.exports = {\n  parser: '@typescript-eslint/parser',\n  plugins: ['@typescript-eslint'],\n  extends: ['eslint:recommended', 'plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended'],\n  parserOptions: {\n    ecmaVersion: 2022,\n    sourceType: 'module',\n  },\n  rules: {\n    '@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars': ['error', { argsIgnorePattern: '^_', varsIgnorePattern: '^_' }],\n  },\n  env: {\n    node: true,\n    es2022: true,\n  },\n};\n```\n\n**4. vitest.config.ts** (/workspace/vitest.config.ts)\n```typescript\nimport { defineConfig } from 'vitest/config';\n\nexport default defineConfig({\n  test: {\n    globals: true,\n    testTimeout: 10000,\n  },\n});\n```\n\n**5. .gitignore** (/workspace/.gitignore)\n```\nnode_modules/\ndist/\n*.tsbuildinfo\n```\n\n### src/ Directory\n- Currently empty except for `.gitkeep` placeholder file\n- This is where implementation files should be created\n- Main API should be exported from `src/index.ts`\n\n### phases/ Directory - 12 Phase Requirements\n\nAll 12 phase requirement files exist in `/workspace/phases/`:\n\n**Phase 1: Basic FIFO Queue** (phase-01.md)\n- Core queue functionality with FIFO ordering\n- Tasks with unique IDs, status tracking, timestamps\n- Pending/processing states\n- Queue length querying\n\n**Phase 2: Named Queues** (phase-02.md)\n- Multiple independent queues by name\n- Default queue support\n- Implicit queue creation\n- Queue name listing\n- Backward compatibility with Phase 1\n\n**Phase 3: Priority** (phase-03.md)\n- Priority levels 1-10 (1=highest, 5=default)\n- Higher-priority tasks returned first\n- FIFO ordering within same priority\n- Per-queue priority management\n\n**Phase 4: Delayed and Scheduled Tasks** (phase-04.md)\n- Task delays in milliseconds or absolute time\n- Delayed tasks not returned until availability time\n- Non-delayed tasks preferred over unavailable delayed tasks\n- Ordering by availability time, then priority, then FIFO\n\n**Phase 5: Retry with Backoff** (phase-05.md)\n- Task completion and failure marking\n- Exponential backoff: `baseDelay * 2^(attempt - 1)`\n- Configurable retries (default 3) and base delay (default 1000ms)\n- Attempt tracking\n- Failed task retention when retries exhausted\n\n**Phase 6: Dead Letter Queue** (phase-06.md)\n- Automatic move to DLQ for permanently failed tasks\n- View dead-lettered tasks per queue\n- Error information and failure count retention\n- Requeue dead-lettered tasks capability\n- Clear DLQ functionality\n\n**Phase 7: Task Dependencies** (phase-07.md)\n- Task-to-task dependencies\n- Blocked status for unmet dependencies\n- Circular dependency detection\n- Non-existent dependency rejection\n- Failed dependencies don't auto-fail dependents\n\n**Phase 8: Concurrency Control** (phase-08.md)\n- Per-queue concurrency limits\n- Returns null when limit reached\n- Freeing slots on task completion/failure\n- Unlimited by default\n- Concurrency awareness with priority ordering\n\n**Phase 9: Progress Tracking and Cancellation** (phase-09.md)\n- Progress reporting (0-100%) with optional message\n- Progress querying\n- Progress change subscriptions\n- Unsubscribe capability\n- Task cancellation for pending/processing states\n- No retry for cancelled tasks\n\n**Phase 10: Recurring Tasks** (phase-10.md)\n- Cron-like scheduling support\n- Simple subset: `*/N * * * *`, `0 * * * *`, `0 0 * * *`\n- Schedule create/remove/list functionality\n- Manual \"tick\" mechanism for testing\n- Regular tasks after enqueue subject to all queue rules\n\n**Phase 11: Middleware Pipeline** (phase-11.md)\n- Per-queue middleware registration\n- Task transformation capability\n- Middleware chain with \"next\" function\n- Optional middleware execution control\n- Error handling in middleware\n- Per-queue handler function registration\n\n**Phase 12: Graceful Shutdown** (phase-12.md)\n- Stop accepting new tasks on shutdown\n- Wait for processing tasks (configurable timeout)\n- Force-cancel on timeout\n- Shutdown callbacks\n- Summary output (completed, cancelled, duration)\n- Multiple shutdown calls safety\n\n### TASK.md Overview\nThe main task documentation at `/workspace/TASK.md` describes the complete project:\n- Building a fully-featured in-memory task queue system\n- 12 incremental phases with growing sophistication\n- No external runtime dependencies (dev dependencies pre-installed)\n- Must build with `npm run build`, pass linting with `npm run lint`\n- API exported from `src/index.ts`\n- Design for extensibility to accommodate later phase requirements\n\n### Development Tools Summary\n- **TypeScript 5.4.0**: Modern JavaScript with type safety (ES2022 target)\n- **Vitest 2.0.0**: Fast unit test framework with 10-second timeout\n- **ESLint 8.56.0**: Code quality enforcement\n- **Node 16+ module resolution**: Modern ES modules support\n\nThis is a greenfield project ready for implementation of a sophisticated task queue system."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a194a6f (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 19815\ntool_uses: 22\nduration_ms: 28742</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eac75e22-58ce-4fc6-896c-8bd62c53d094","uuid":"3e29d04f-b8f9-4b4f-8581-fb64190ed2db","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the entire codebase structure. I need to understand:\n1. What files exist in the project root and src/ directory\n2. All phase requirement files in phases/*.md\n3. The package.json configuration\n4. The tsconfig.json configuration\n5. Any existing source files\n\nBe very thorough - read every file you find. List the complete di