+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_018a4ibdhkwRp5Z65YGJHZwi","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01LZbUxCw5VLYhZdPmTSL6sT","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-08-task-queue-system.md","content":"# Task Queue System Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Build a fully-featured in-memory task queue system with 12 phases of increasing sophistication.\n\n**Architecture:** A single `TaskQueue` class manages multiple named queues internally. Each named queue is a `Queue` object holding tasks sorted by priority/FIFO. Tasks are represented by a `Task` interface tracking ID, status, payload, priority, timestamps, retries, dependencies, and progress. The system uses an event-based approach for progress notifications and middleware pipelines.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript 5.4, Vitest 2.0, Node 16+ ESM modules, no external runtime dependencies.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n```\nsrc/\n  index.ts          - Public API exports\n  task-queue.ts      - Main TaskQueue class (orchestrator)\n  queue.ts           - Individual named queue logic\n  task.ts            - Task interface and factory\n  types.ts           - Shared types/interfaces\n  middleware.ts       - Middleware pipeline\n  scheduler.ts       - Recurring task scheduler (cron)\n  utils.ts           - UUID generation, helpers\n```\n\n### Task 1: Project Setup and Types\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/types.ts`\n- Create: `src/utils.ts`\n- Create: `src/index.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Create types.ts with all core interfaces**\n\n```typescript\n// src/types.ts\nexport type TaskStatus = 'pending' | 'processing' | 'completed' | 'failed' | 'cancelled' | 'blocked';\n\nexport interface Task<T = unknown> {\n  id: string;\n  status: TaskStatus;\n  payload: T;\n  priority: number;\n  createdAt: Date;\n  updatedAt: Date;\n  availableAt: Date;\n  queueName: string;\n  attempts: number;\n  maxRetries: number;\n  backoffDelay: number;\n  lastError?: string;\n  dependencies: string[];\n  resolvedDependencies: Set<string>;\n  progress: number;\n  progressMessage?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface TaskOptions {\n  priority?: number;\n  delay?: number;\n  availableAt?: Date;\n  maxRetries?: number;\n  backoffDelay?: number;\n  dependencies?: string[];\n}\n\nexport interface AddTaskOptions extends TaskOptions {\n  queue?: string;\n}\n\nexport type MiddlewareFn = (task: Task, next: () => Promise<void>) => Promise<void>;\nexport type HandlerFn = (task: Task) => Promise<void>;\nexport type ProgressListener = (progress: number, message?: string) => void;\n\nexport interface ScheduleEntry {\n  id: string;\n  cronExpression: string;\n  queueName: string;\n  payload: unknown;\n  taskOptions?: TaskOptions;\n  lastRun?: Date;\n}\n\nexport interface ShutdownOptions {\n  timeout?: number;\n}\n\nexport interface ShutdownResult {\n  completed: number;\n  cancelled: number;\n  duration: number;\n}\n\nexport const DEFAULT_QUEUE = 'default';\nexport const DEFAULT_PRIORITY = 5;\nexport const DEFAULT_MAX_RETRIES = 3;\nexport const DEFAULT_BACKOFF_DELAY = 1000;\n```\n\n**Step 2: Create utils.ts with UUID generation**\n\n```typescript\n// src/utils.ts\nimport { randomUUID } from 'node:crypto';\n\nexport function generateId(): string {\n  return randomUUID();\n}\n```\n\n**Step 3: Create initial index.ts**\n\n```typescript\n// src/index.ts - will grow as we implement\nexport { TaskQueue } from './task-queue.js';\nexport type { Task, TaskStatus, TaskOptions, AddTaskOptions, ShutdownOptions, ShutdownResult, ScheduleEntry, MiddlewareFn, HandlerFn, ProgressListener } from './types.js';\n```\n\n**Step 4: Verify build compiles (after task-queue.ts exists)**\n\n### Task 2: Phase 1 & 2 - Basic FIFO Queue + Named Queues\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/task-queue.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/phases-1-2.test.ts`\n\nImplement together since named queues are a natural extension of basic queue.\n\n**Core implementation:**\n\nThe TaskQueue class holds a `Map<string, Task[]>` for pending tasks per queue, plus a global `Map<string, Task>` for all tasks by ID. `addTask()` creates a task and pushes to the named queue. `getNextTask(queueName?)` finds the oldest pending task in that queue, marks it processing, returns it.\n\n### Task 3: Phase 3 - Priority\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/task-queue.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/phase-3.test.ts`\n\nSort tasks by priority (ascending, 1=highest), then by creation order. Validate priority 1-10.\n\n### Task 4: Phase 4 - Delayed Tasks\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/task-queue.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/phase-4.test.ts`\n\nAdd `delay` and `availableAt` support. When getting next task, filter out tasks where `availableAt > now`. Order: available first, then by priority, then FIFO.\n\n### Task 5: Phase 5 - Retry with Backoff\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/task-queue.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/phase-5.test.ts`\n\nAdd `completeTask(id)` and `failTask(id, error?)`. On fail with retries remaining: increment attempts, set delay with exponential backoff, re-enqueue as pending with new availableAt.\n\n### Task 6: Phase 6 - Dead Letter Queue\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/task-queue.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/phase-6.test.ts`\n\nWhen retries exhausted on fail, move to DLQ. Add `getDeadLetters(queueName)`, `requeueDeadLetter(taskId)`, `clearDeadLetters(queueName)`.\n\n### Task 7: Phase 7 - Task Dependencies\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/task-queue.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/phase-7.test.ts`\n\nTasks with dependencies start as 'blocked'. On task completion, check all blocked tasks and resolve dependencies. Detect circular deps at add time with DFS.\n\n### Task 8: Phase 8 - Concurrency Control\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/task-queue.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/phase-8.test.ts`\n\nTrack active processing count per queue. `setConcurrency(queueName, limit)`. `getNextTask` returns null if at limit.\n\n### Task 9: Phase 9 - Progress and Cancellation\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/task-queue.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/phase-9.test.ts`\n\n`updateProgress(taskId, percent, message?)`, `getProgress(taskId)`, `onProgress(taskId, listener)`, `offProgress(taskId, listener)`, `cancelTask(taskId)`.\n\n### Task 10: Phase 10 - Recurring Tasks\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/scheduler.ts`\n- Modify: `src/task-queue.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/phase-10.test.ts`\n\nSimple cron parser for the subset. `addSchedule()`, `removeSchedule()`, `listSchedules()`, `tick(now?)`.\n\n### Task 11: Phase 11 - Middleware Pipeline\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/task-queue.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/phase-11.test.ts`\n\n`use(queueName, middleware)`, `setHandler(queueName, handler)`, `processTask(queueName)` runs middleware chain then handler.\n\n### Task 12: Phase 12 - Graceful Shutdown\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/task-queue.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/phase-12.test.ts`\n\n`shutdown(options?)` returns Promise<ShutdownResult>. Sets flag to reject new tasks, waits for processing tasks, force-cancels on timeout, runs callbacks.\n\n### Task 13: Final Build and Lint Verification\n\nRun `npm run build` and `npm run lint` to ensure everything compiles and passes lint.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":127,"cache_read_input_tokens":24157,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":127},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eac75e22-58ce-4fc6-896c-8bd62c53d094","uuid":"57fbee30-de0a-4fcb-b532-14dce977087e"}
+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LZbUxCw5VLYhZdPmTSL6sT","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-08-task-queue-system.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eac75e22-58ce-4fc6-896c-8bd62c53d094","uuid":"b529cb71-3d0a-442d-a3f2-61513a49906a","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-08-task-queue-system.md","content":"# Task Queue System Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Build a fully-featured in-memory task queue system with 12 phases of increasing sophistication.\n\n**Architecture:** A single `TaskQueue` class manages multiple named queues internally. Each named queue is a `Queue` object holding tasks sorted by priority/FIFO. Tasks are represented by a `Task` interface tracking ID, status, payload, priority, timestamps, retries, dependencies, and progress. The system uses an event-based approach for progress notifications and middleware pipelines.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript 5.4, Vitest 2.0, Node 16+ ESM modules, no external runtime dependencies.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n```\nsrc/\n  index.ts          - Public API exports\n  task-queue.ts      - Main TaskQueue class (orchestrator)\n  queue.ts           - Individual named queue logic\n  task.ts            - Task interface and factory\n  types.ts           - Shared types/interfaces\n  middleware.ts       - Middleware pipeline\n  scheduler.ts       - Recurring task scheduler (cron)\n  utils.ts           - UUID generation, helpers\n```\n\n### Task 1: Project Setup and Types\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/types.ts`\n- Create: `src/utils.ts`\n- Create: `src/index.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Create types.ts with all core interfaces**\n\n```typescript\n// src/types.ts\nexport type TaskStatus = 'pending' | 'processing' | 'completed' | 'failed' | 'cancelled' | 'blocked';\n\nexport interface Task<T = unknown> {\n  id: string;\n  status: TaskStatus;\n  payload: T;\n  priority: number;\n  createdAt: Date;\n  updatedAt: Date;\n  availableAt: Date;\n  queueName: string;\n  attempts: number;\n  maxRetries: number;\n  backoffDelay: number;\n  lastError?: string;\n  dependencies: string[];\n  resolvedDependencies: Set<string>;\n  progress: number;\n  progressMessage?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface TaskOptions {\n  priority?: number;\n  delay?: number;\n  availableAt?: Date;\n  maxRetries?: number;\n  backoffDelay?: number;\n  dependencies?: string[];\n}\n\nexport interface AddTaskOptions extends TaskOptions {\n  queue?: string;\n}\n\nexport type MiddlewareFn = (task: Task, next: () => Promise<void>) => Promise<void>;\nexport type HandlerFn = (task: Task) => Promise<void>;\nexport type ProgressListener = (progress: number, message?: string) => void;\n\nexport interface ScheduleEntry {\n  id: string;\n  cronExpression: string;\n  queueName: string;\n  payload: unknown;\n  taskOptions?: TaskOptions;\n  lastRun?: Date;\n}\n\nexport interface ShutdownOptions {\n  timeout?: number;\n}\n\nexport interface ShutdownResult {\n  completed: number;\n  cancelled: number;\n  duration: number;\n}\n\nexport const DEFAULT_QUEUE = 'default';\nexport const DEFAULT_PRIORITY = 5;\nexport const DEFAULT_MAX_RETRIES = 3;\nexport const DEFAULT_BACKOFF_DELAY = 1000;\n```\n\n**Step 2: Create utils.ts with UUID generation**\n\n```typescript\n// src/utils.ts\nimport { randomUUID } from 'node:crypto';\n\nexport function generateId(): string {\n  return randomUUID();\n}\n```\n\n**Step 3: Create initial index.ts**\n\n```typescript\n// src/index.ts - will grow as we implement\nexport { TaskQueue } from './task-queue.js';\nexport type { Task, TaskStatus, TaskOptions, AddTaskOptions, ShutdownOptions, ShutdownResult, ScheduleEntry, MiddlewareFn, HandlerFn, ProgressListener } from './types.js';\n```\n\n**Step 4: Verify build compiles (after task-queue.ts exists)**\n\n### Task 2: Phase 1 & 2 - Basic FIFO Queue + Named Queues\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/task-queue.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/phases-1-2.test.ts`\n\nImplement together since named queues are a natural extension of basic queue.\n\n**Core implementation:**\n\nThe TaskQueue class holds a `Map<string, Task[]>` for pending tasks per queue, plus a global `Map<string, Task>` for all tasks by ID. `addTask()` creates a task and pushes to the named queue. `getNextTask(queueName?)` finds the oldest pending task in that queue, marks it processing, returns it.\n\n### Task 3: Phase 3 - Priority\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/task-queue.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/phase-3.test.ts`\n\nSort tasks by priority (ascending, 1=highest), then by creation order. Validate priority 1-10.\n\n### Task 4: Phase 4 - Delayed Tasks\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/task-queue.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/phase-4.test.ts`\n\nAdd `delay` and `availableAt` support. When getting next task, filter out tasks where `availableAt > now`. Order: available first, then by priority, then FIFO.\n\n### Task 5: Phase 5 - Retry with Backoff\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/task-queue.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/phase-5.test.ts`\n\nAdd `completeTask(id)` and `failTask(id, error?)`. On fail with retries remaining: increment attempts, set delay with exponential backoff, re-enqueue as pending with new availableAt.\n\n### Task 6: Phase 6 - Dead Letter Queue\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/task-queue.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/phase-6.test.ts`\n\nWhen retries exhausted on fail, move to DLQ. Add `getDeadLetters(queueName)`, `requeueDeadLetter(taskId)`, `clearDeadLetters(queueName)`.\n\n### Task 7: Phase 7 - Task Dependencies\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/task-queue.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/phase-7.test.ts`\n\nTasks with dependencies start as 'blocked'. On task completion, check all blocked tasks and resolve dependencies. Detect circular deps at add time with DFS.\n\n### Task 8: Phase 8 - Concurrency Control\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/task-queue.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/phase-8.test.ts`\n\nTrack active processing count per queue. `setConcurrency(queueName, limit)`. `getNextTask` returns null if at limit.\n\n### Task 9: Phase 9 - Progress and Cancellation\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/task-queue.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/phase-9.test.ts`\n\n`updateProgress(taskId, percent, message?)`, `getProgress(taskId)`, `onProgress(taskId, listener)`, `offProgress(taskId, listener)`, `cancelTask(taskId)`.\n\n### Task 10: Phase 10 - Recurring Tasks\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/scheduler.ts`\n- Modify: `src/task-queue.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/phase-10.test.ts`\n\nSimple cron parser for the subset. `addSchedule()`, `removeSchedule()`, `listSchedules()`, `tick(now?)`.\n\n### Task 11: Phase 11 - Middleware Pipeline\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/task-queue.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/phase-11.test.ts`\n\n`use(queueName, middleware)`, `setHandler(queueName, handler)`, `processTask(queueName)` runs middleware chain then handler.\n\n### Task 12: Phase 12 - Graceful Shutdown\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/task-queue.ts`\n- Create: `src/tests/phase-12.test.ts`\n\n`shutdown(options?)` returns Promise<ShutdownResult>. Sets flag to reject new tasks, waits for processing tasks, force-cancels on timeout, runs callbacks.\n\n### Task 13: Final Build and Lint Verification\n\nRun `npm run build` and `npm run lint` to ensure everything compiles and passes lint.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
